  "texts": [
    "Potential benefits and risks of ChatGPT in educational arenaPrevious studies [3,20,27,34,48], examined the benefits and threats posed by ChatGPT in the educational setting.",
    "For instance, Tajik and Tajik.",
    "[48] describe the potential qualities of GPT from three perspectives: those of the student (e.g., acting as a learning companion for an intelligence tutor system), the teacher (e.g., lessening workload by automating tasks in planning, instruction, assessment, and interaction with students and stakeholders), and the system (e.g., streamlining administrative tasks and saving time for admission process and management).",
    "It can be used to create educational content, enhance student engagement and interaction, and personalise learning experiences, according to Kasneci et al. [27].On the other hand, Atlas [3] remarks that there are five potential challenges and limitations faced when using ChatGPT in higher education which are (1) perpetuating societal biases and discrimination, (2) being used in ways that are not in line with human values and beliefs; (3) being used in ways that are harmful (such as creating a surveillance state); (4) a lack of understanding of human emotions, intentions and moral reasoning; (5) poor quality of output leading to inaccurate responses.",
    "Other challenges include copyright concerns, data privacy and security issues [4]."
  ]
}